Personal Statement   
Highly motivated and enthusiastic self-starter with a broad range of skills in all aspects of 
administration. I possess a keen eye for detail ensuring all duties are carried out in a timely 
and effective manner. I believe I would be an asset to any team bringing with me a wealth of 
knowledge, innovative ideas, people skills and with the ability to work under pressure. 
Seeking employment with a progressive company that calls for hard work and creativity and 
offers opportunities for professional development.  
Employment History:   
Sweet Freedom Ltd - January 2020- Present 
Office Manager/ PA to Founder 
• Day to day adhoc tasks for founders  
• Sending buyers samples 
• Arrange training courses for staff members 
• Working with the accounts team to ensure all invoice are correct and paid. 
• Ensuring contracts and certificates are renewed and we are meeting their requirements  
• Manage website - checking daily that it is running correctly, adding new products, 
recipes, reviews and press cuttings 
• Managing the online shop - Take and fulfil online orders, arrange delivery, pack, send 
and communicate with customers 
• Liaise with buyers - very often receive enquiries about our products, if they can sell our 
products, sending samples and liaising with the sales team to set them up as a customer. 
• Choosing competition winners, contacting them and sending out their prizes 
• Stock control 
• Customer service - customer enquiries/complaints  
• Regular communication with sales teams and manufacturers - sending samples, chasing 
emails  
• Booking deliveries 
 
Business Central Ltd   - May 2018 to January 2020- Redundancy  
  Office Manager/ PA to CEO  
• Responsible for overseeing CEO’s calendar, liaising with internal and external 
stakeholders efficiently sending meeting requests and managing last minute 
cancellations  
• Accurately recording minutes from meetings.  
• Ensuring CEO is prepared for meetings  
• Recruited and managed 2 cleaners and ensuring cleanliness standards are maintained  
• Helping implement and support Growth Partners on their Health & Safety guidelines. This 
includes creating induction material, delivering a Health & Safety induction programme to 
new employees and implementation of related procedures  
• Supporting with GDPR needs 
• Assisting and supporting in the planning of the Company’s events  
• Liaising with overseas office in order for purchase sign off, ensuring accuracy and 
attention to detail with each purchase.  

• Assist and support with cost approval for payment of services/products the business 
might require  
• Coordinating with architects for office refit completion, this includes supervision of 
contractors  
• Ensuring all security needs are met and making sure all access cards and office keys are 
provided to the relevant people  
• Working with the marketing team to create and order all the merchandising for the 
company 
 
 Additional duties  
• Creating presentations for health and safety and equality and diversity inductions  
• Organising all the birthdays and anniversaries cards and gifts   
• Maintaining the allocated parking  
• Working with the HR team with all culture-based events and awareness days 
  
Whilst working at Business Central I received employee of the month for April
